<------------------------------Frame by Frame Engine:------------------------------------->
 The FBF portion of Slide Flick focuses on recording shape properties per frame. This is stored in customxmlparts but during runtime it is stored in a quickly read object collection
To best understand FBF for future me I will write out the collections and properties I plan to hold and then the process for a New Scene, Record a Frame, Add new Shape, Scrubbing, and Playback

Collections and Properties:
* Used Shape Collection (Position): holds all IDs of shapes that have had one or more animations. We are keeping them separate because we should not try to add additional updates that are not needed.
* Used Shape Collection (Scale): Holds all IDS of shapes that had at least one scale change. All scale change shape IDs will automatically be added to the used shapes position collection because translation happens when scale happens.
* Used Shape Collection (Visibility): Holds all shapes that had any kind of visibility change. this is separate because most shapes that experience visibility will not typically change position or scale apart from a group carrying them.
* Frame Data Collection (Position). Contains all frames for an animation. Each value is nothing but a delimited list of shape IDs that have movements of top, left or rotation.
